                                                                    <p class="no_name">He said work on the wider economic plan âwill proceed at place, ready for implementation later this yearâ.</p>
                                                        <p class="no_name">âAn ambitious and comprehensive response to an unprecedented crisis felt by every family, business and individual in the country,â he said.</p>
                                                        <p class="no_name">âThe greatest strength of our country has always been the skills of our people â¦ our determination is to work in partnership with the Irish peopleâ in an effort to protect and create jobs.</p>
                                                        <h4 class="crosshead">Unemployment payment</h4><p class="no_name">As part of the package after September there will be three rates, based on pre-unemployment earnings, instead of the current two.</p>
                                                        <p class="no_name">There will be a new top rate of â¬300 a week, a middle rate of â¬250, and the basic â¬203 per week rate, equivalent to the regular rate of unemployment benefit.</p>
                        <div class="adwrapper">
                <div id='div-gpt-ad-InContent-2' class="ad-inline-article">
                    <script>
                        googletag.cmd.push(function () {
                            googletag.display('div-gpt-ad-InContent-2');
                        });
                    </script>
                </div>
            </div>
                                                        <p class="no_name">The long-awaited plan was published by the Government in Dublin Castle after a Cabinet meeting on Thursday with a package that included capital spending, welfare and employment supports, grants and tax cuts.</p>
                                                        <p class="no_name">TÃ¡naiste Leo Varadkar said about 800,000 people had benefited from the pandemic unemployment payment at some point. At its peak, 600,000 people were on the payment.</p>
                                                        <p class="no_name">He confirmed the temporary wage subsidy scheme was being extended to March, and will be open to firms not currently participating as well as workers not currently covered, such as seasonal workers.</p>
                                                        <figure class="inline__content inline__content--image"> 
 <img alt="Taoiseach MicheÃ¡l Martin, TÃ¡naiste Leo Varadkar and Minister for Climate Action Eamon Ryan at Dublin Castle today for the post cabinet press briefing. Photograph: Julien Behal Photography" height="349" src="/polopoly_fs/1.4312019!/image/image.jpg_gen/derivatives/landscape_620/image.jpg" width="620"> 
 <figcaption>
   Taoiseach MicheÃ¡l Martin, TÃ¡naiste Leo Varadkar and Minister for Climate Action Eamon Ryan at Dublin Castle today for the post cabinet press briefing. Photograph: Julien Behal Photography 
 </figcaption> 
</figure><p class="no_name">Mr Varadkar confirmed a six month two per cent cut in the rate of VAT, from 23 per cent to 21 per cent, and a six month commercial rates holiday.</p>
                                                        <p class="no_name">A further â¬300 million in grants for small and medium enterprises, with the maximum lifted to â¬25,000. He said this would be especially useful to rural businesses, and the businesses, which had already received a grant could apply for a top up. B&amp;Bs, charities and ratable sports businesses, previously kept out of the scheme, will now be eligible.</p>
                                                        <p class="no_name">He said he wanted to pay tribute to the business people of <a href="/news">Ireland</a> who had displayed âremarkable grit, determination and adaptability in the face of unprecedented challenges.â</p>
                                                        <p class="no_name">To the unemployed, he said, the package âcreates a path back to your old job or to a new oneâ.</p>
                                                        <p class="no_name">âBacking business and backing workers,â he said. âWeâll get through this pandemic together, and through this economic crisis together.â</p>
                                                        <p class="no_name">Cheaper loans would be made available through the credit guarantee scheme, with a particular emphasis on sectors such as life sciences, and industries focused on decarbonisation and digitalisation.</p>
                        <div class="adwrapper">
                <div id='div-gpt-ad-InContent-3' class="ad-inline-article">
                    <script>
                        googletag.cmd.push(function () {
                            googletag.display('div-gpt-ad-InContent-3');
